01:35:28,060 --> 01:35:30,260
This is the picture of a meson.

2151
01:35:30,260 --> 01:35:34,260
The other ingredient that is in quantum chromodynamics

2152
01:35:34,260 --> 01:35:36,140
is that three quarks can exist.

2153
01:35:36,140 --> 01:35:38,380
This doesn't explain three quarks.

2154
01:35:38,380 --> 01:35:41,020
The three quarks are explained by a mathematical fact.

2155
01:35:41,020 --> 01:35:46,020
The flux lines can come together in threes.

2156
01:35:46,020 --> 01:35:49,020
Quark, quark, quark.

2157
01:35:49,020 --> 01:35:53,020
And, uh, but that's not

2158
01:35:53,020 --> 01:35:57,020
too surprising because three quarks, again,

2159
01:35:57,020 --> 01:35:59,020
make a neutral object.

2160
01:35:59,020 --> 01:36:02,020
Three quarks, again, make a neutral object.

2161
01:36:02,020 --> 01:36:04,020
And that means that if you have three quarks,

2162
01:36:04,020 --> 01:36:06,020
there'll be no net lines coming out of it.

2163
01:36:06,020 --> 01:36:07,520
So somehow the lines are forced to

2164
01:36:07,520 --> 01:36:09,020
come out of each one of them,

2165
01:36:09,020 --> 01:36:10,020
have to...

2166
01:36:11,020 --> 01:36:13,020
be able to cancel each other.

2167
01:36:13,020 --> 01:36:15,020
That's quantum chromodynamics.

2168
01:36:15,020 --> 01:36:17,020
It's based on the SU group.

2169
01:36:17,020 --> 01:36:19,020
And it's called a gauge theory.

2170
01:36:19,020 --> 01:36:21,020
A gauge theory is simply

2171
01:36:21,020 --> 01:36:23,020
any theory where the conserved quantities

2172
01:36:23,020 --> 01:36:27,020
are coupled to a Maxwell-like field,

2173
01:36:27,020 --> 01:36:31,020
are coupled to a field similar to photons.

2174
01:36:31,020 --> 01:36:33,020
It has a deeper meaning

2175
01:36:33,020 --> 01:36:35,020
than that, but for our purposes,

2176
01:36:35,020 --> 01:36:38,020
any time there is a

2177
01:36:38,020 --> 01:36:41,020
conserved quantity analogous to electric charge,

2178
01:36:41,020 --> 01:36:48,020
which functions as the source of a photon-like field,

2179
01:36:48,020 --> 01:36:50,020
photon-like field, a gluon-like field,

2180
01:36:50,020 --> 01:36:52,020
that's called a gauge theory.

2181
01:36:52,020 --> 01:36:55,020
The gauge theories are always based on symmetries.

2182
01:36:55,020 --> 01:36:56,020
Why are they based on symmetries?

2183
01:36:56,020 --> 01:37:00,020
Because they're based on the idea of conserved charge.

2184
01:37:00,020 --> 01:37:05,020
And conserved charge means a symmetry of some kind.

2185
01:37:05,020 --> 01:37:07,020
Incidentally, why...

2186
01:37:07,020 --> 01:37:09,020
What's the connection between conservation and logic?

2187
01:37:09,020 --> 01:37:13,020
Between conservation and lines of flux.

2188
01:37:13,020 --> 01:37:17,020
Conservation and lines of flux are intimately connected.

2189
01:37:21,020 --> 01:37:25,020
If you have a rule, for example, in electrodynamics,

2190
01:37:25,020 --> 01:37:27,520
that every charged particle has to

2191
01:37:27,520 --> 01:37:30,020
be the source of lines of flux,

2192
01:37:32,020 --> 01:37:34,020
and that lines of flux

2193
01:37:34,020 --> 01:37:36,020
can only end on charged particles,

2194
01:37:36,020 --> 01:37:39,020
then charge has to be conserved.

2195
01:37:39,020 --> 01:37:40,020
There's no way...

2196
01:37:40,020 --> 01:37:43,020
Remember, these lines of force go off to infinity.

2197
01:37:43,020 --> 01:37:44,520
Well, you could say, I

2198
01:37:44,520 --> 01:37:46,020
could make this charge suddenly disappear

2199
01:37:46,020 --> 01:37:48,520
if I allow the lines

2200
01:37:48,520 --> 01:37:51,020
of flux to simultaneously all disappear.

2201
01:37:51,020 --> 01:37:55,020
But that would violate the speed of light constraint.

2202
01:37:55,020 --> 01:37:57,520
You would be able to

2203
01:37:57,520 --> 01:38:00,020
send a message arbitrarily far distance

2204
01:38:00,020 --> 01:38:03,020
if, by simply removing that charge,

2205
01:38:03,020 --> 01:38:09,020
you suddenly changed the field at infinity.

2206
01:38:09,020 --> 01:38:11,020
The fact that you cannot send a

2207
01:38:11,020 --> 01:38:13,020
signal faster than the speed of light

2208
01:38:13,020 --> 01:38:16,020
tells you that you can't remove this charge.

2209
01:38:16,020 --> 01:38:17,020
Why?

2210
01:38:17,020 --> 01:38:19,020
Because it's sort of anchored

2211
01:38:19,020 --> 01:38:21,020
by the flux lines at infinity,

2212
01:38:21,020 --> 01:38:24,020
and if you could remove it,

2213
01:38:24,020 --> 01:38:26,020
either one of two things.

2214
01:38:26,020 --> 01:38:29,020
Either you would send a sudden signal far away

2215
01:38:29,020 --> 01:38:31,020
that the charge wasn't there by removing the field,

2216
01:38:31,020 --> 01:38:33,020
or you would be left

2217
01:38:33,020 --> 01:38:35,020
over with these lines of flux

2218
01:38:35,020 --> 01:38:37,020
that don't end on charges.

2219
01:38:37,020 --> 01:38:40,020
So if lines of flux have to end on charges,

2220
01:38:40,020 --> 01:38:43,020
then that's tantamount to saying that

2221
01:38:43,020 --> 01:38:46,020
the sources of the field are conserved,

2222
01:38:46,020 --> 01:38:51,020
which, in another language, says there must be a symmetry.

2223
01:38:51,020 --> 01:38:56,020
So some symmetries are connected with photon-like fields

2224
01:38:56,020 --> 01:38:59,020
which give rise to lines of flux.

2225
01:38:59,020 --> 01:39:02,020
Those theories are called gauge theories.

2226
01:39:02,020 --> 01:39:05,020
And you can't even imagine,

2227
01:39:05,020 --> 01:39:07,020
without breaking the rules of physics,

2228
01:39:07,020 --> 01:39:09,020
without breaking the rules of a theory,

2229
01:39:09,020 --> 01:39:10,520
what it would mean for

2230
01:39:10,520 --> 01:39:12,020
the charge not to be conserved,

2231
01:39:12,020 --> 01:39:16,020
because the rules of a theory attach the charged particles

2232
01:39:16,020 --> 01:39:19,020
to the lines of force.

2233
01:39:19,020 --> 01:39:22,020
Okay, that's quantum chromodynamics.

2234
01:39:22,020 --> 01:39:24,020
Now we've actually gone,

2235
01:39:24,020 --> 01:39:26,020
either depending on how you count,

2236
01:39:26,020 --> 01:39:28,520
either two-thirds or three-quarters of

2237
01:39:28,520 --> 01:39:31,020
the way through the standard model,

2238
01:39:31,020 --> 01:39:35,020
we've gone through nine generators, if you like.

2239
01:39:35,020 --> 01:39:37,020
The eight generators of SU3,

2240
01:39:37,020 --> 01:39:40,020
the electric charge,

2241
01:39:40,020 --> 01:39:41,520
the electric charge, which is

2242
01:39:41,520 --> 01:39:43,020
not the ninth generator of U3.

2243
01:39:43,020 --> 01:39:47,020
The electric charge, those are nine conserved quantities.

2244
01:39:47,020 --> 01:39:50,020
They couple to the nine gauge fields,

2245
01:39:50,020 --> 01:39:53,020
the eight gluons and the photon.

2246
01:39:53,020 --> 01:39:56,020
The standard model has three more generators,

2247
01:39:56,020 --> 01:39:58,020
which we will talk about.

2248
01:39:58,020 --> 01:40:00,020
So we've got nine out of twelve.

2249
01:40:00,020 --> 01:40:03,020
That's three-quarters.

2250
01:40:03,020 --> 01:40:04,520
The other way of counting

2251
01:40:04,520 --> 01:40:06,020
is to say we studied SU3,

2252
01:40:07,020 --> 01:40:10,020
that's quantum chromodynamics.

2253
01:40:10,020 --> 01:40:14,020
We've studied U1, that's electrodynamics.

2254
01:40:14,020 --> 01:40:18,020
The standard model is SU3 cross SU2 cross U1.

2255
01:40:18,020 --> 01:40:20,020
We're missing the SU2.

2256
01:40:20,020 --> 01:40:23,020
The SU2, it's not angular momentum.

2257
01:40:23,020 --> 01:40:27,020
There's another ingredient in the standard model called SU2.

2258
01:40:27,020 --> 01:40:30,020
We'll start to take up SU2 next time.

2259
01:40:30,020 --> 01:40:33,020
We've covered a lot of ground,

2260
01:40:33,020 --> 01:40:36,020
and I think in about two more lectures,

2261
01:40:36,020 --> 01:40:40,020
we can probably finish off the basic structure

2262
01:40:40,020 --> 01:40:44,020
of the standard model, SU3 cross SU2 cross U1,

2263
01:40:44,020 --> 01:40:47,020
put it together into a package,

2264
01:40:47,020 --> 01:40:49,520
and I think the other

2265
01:40:49,520 --> 01:40:52,020
element that we need, of course,

2266
01:40:52,020 --> 01:40:54,020
is the Higgs field.

2267
01:40:54,020 --> 01:40:57,020
The Higgs field plays an important role there.

2268
01:40:57,020 --> 01:41:03,020
But I would say within about three lectures,

2269
01:41:03,020 --> 01:41:05,020
we will have the working parts of the standard model.

2270
01:41:05,020 --> 01:41:06,520
And then we can start to

2271
01:41:06,520 --> 01:41:08,020
explore what the puzzles of it are,

2272
01:41:08,020 --> 01:41:09,520
why people think we have

2273
01:41:09,520 --> 01:41:11,020
to go beyond the standard model,

2274
01:41:11,020 --> 01:41:12,520
and why people think there are

2275
01:41:12,520 --> 01:41:14,020
going to be interesting new things

2276
01:41:14,020 --> 01:41:16,020
discovered at CERN.

2277
01:41:16,020 --> 01:41:19,020
I think that's what we want to get.

2278
01:41:19,020 --> 01:41:21,020
Okay, good.

2279
01:41:21,020 --> 01:41:24,020
For more, please visit us at stanford.edu.

